== 歷史 ==
From independence in 1960 until 1999 it was divided into {{tsl|en|prefectures of Chad||14 ''préfectures''}}. These were replaced in 1999 by {{tsl|en|departments of Chad||28 ''départements''}}. The country was reorganized again in 2002 to produce 18 ''régions''.  In 2008, a further four ''régions'' were created, increasing the number to 22. Ennedi Region was split into Ennedi-Est and Ennedi-Ouest in 2012, producing the current 23 regions.<ref name=statoids>{{cite web |last=Law |first=Gwillim |url=http://www.statoids.com/utd.html |title=Regions of Chad |website=Statoids |access-date=15 June 2015 |archive-date=2019-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190106233954/http://www.statoids.com/utd.html%20 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=ordonnance>{{cite web |last=Déby |first=Idriss |author-link=Idriss Déby |url=http://sgg-tchad.org/ordonnances/ORD_70001.pdf |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160521195604/http://sgg-tchad.org/ordonnances/ORD_70001.pdf |archive-date=2016-05-21 |title=Ordonnance No. 27/PR/2012 |publisher=Republic of Chad |date=4 September 2012 |access-date=14 June 2015 }}</ref>

